Readings: Database Administration
A database is a systematic collection of data and they support electronic storage and manipulation of data. Databases make data management easy. SQL is the standard language for dealing with relational databases. DBMS stands for database management system. There are four major types of DBMSâ€™s namely Hierarchical, Network, Relational, Object-Oriented. The most widely used DBMS is the relational model that saves data in table format. It uses SQL as the standard query language. SQL language is used to query a database. The database approach has many advantages when it comes to storing data compared to the traditional flat file based system. 
